.TH NVFLUX 1 "2026" "nvflux 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nvflux \- NVIDIA GPU clock profile manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nvflux
.I command
.SH DESCRIPTION
nvflux is a setuid-root helper that locks or unlocks NVIDIA GPU memory and core
clocks via
.BR nvidia-smi (1)
without requiring the user to invoke
.BR sudo
each time.
Clock tiers are queried live from the driver; no values are hard-coded.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B ultra
Lock both the memory clock and the GPU core clock to their maximum supported tier.
Equivalent to PowerMizer \(lqPrefer Maximum Performance\(rq.
Requires Volta+ GPU.
.TP
.B performance
Lock the memory clock to the highest supported tier.
GPU core clock remains driver-managed.
.TP
.B balanced
Lock the memory clock to the mid-range supported tier.
GPU core clock remains driver-managed.
.TP
.B powersave
Lock the memory clock to the lowest supported tier.
GPU core clock remains driver-managed.
.TP
.B auto
Remove all clock locks; return to fully driver-managed (Adaptive) mode.
.TP
.B reset
Alias for
.BR auto .
.TP
.B status
Print the last saved profile name.  Does not require root.
.TP
.B clock
Print the current memory clock in MHz.  Does not require root.
.TP
.B \-\-restore
Re-apply the last saved profile.  Useful in autostart scripts.
.TP
.BR \-v , " \-\-version"
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h , " \-\-help"
Show usage summary and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/nvflux/state
Per-user state file recording the last applied profile.
Owned by the real UID (not root), mode 0600.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Operational error (clock lock failed, no saved profile, etc.).
.TP
2
nvidia-smi not found.
.TP
3
Not running as root (effective UID ≠ 0).
.TP
4
No NVIDIA GPU detected or driver not loaded.
.TP
5
Unknown command.
.SH NOTES
nvflux must be installed setuid root.
.B scripts/install.sh
performs this automatically.
.PP
On Hopper+ GPUs,
.B \-\-lock-memory-clocks
is unsupported; nvflux falls back to
.B \-\-lock-memory-clocks-deferred
automatically and prints a note.
The setting takes effect after a kernel module reload.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nvidia-smi (1),
.BR nvidia-settings (1)
.PP
nvidia-smi documentation: https://docs.nvidia.com/deploy/nvidia-smi/index.html
.SH AUTHORS
nvflux contributors.
